<body class='tk-publico'>

	{{> base/header }}
	
	<main id='content'>
		<h1 class='tk-canela hed'>Style Guide</h1>
		<p>Welcome to The Pudding style guide. Use this as a reference to structure your HTML and CSS, and follow our best practices.</p>

		<section id='usage'>
			<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Usage</h3>
			<p>Everything you need is already included in your new project template. Simply follow these guidelines and use the proper CSS classes outlined and you should be good to go.</p>
		</section>
		
		<section id='typography'>
			<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Typography</h3>
			<h4>Fonts</h4>
			<p>
				Fonts are loaded async and use the <a href='https://www.zachleat.com/web/comprehensive-webfonts/#fout-class' target='_blank'>FOUT</a> practice. We have three font families:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Headlines:</strong> Canela (class name: <em>tk-canela</em>)</li>
				<li><strong>Copy:</strong> Publico Text (class name: <em>tk-publico</em>)</li>
				<li><strong>Graphics / Captions:</strong> Atlas Grotesk (class name: <em>tk-atlas</em>)</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Simply include the class on the element, and all children will inherit it. Publico is included on the body tag by default.
			</p>
			<div class='example'>
<pre><code>&lt;p class='tk-canela'&gt;Test&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>
			</div>

			<p>Use the <em>font-weight</em> CSS property to set the weight.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Canela:</strong> 300, 700</li>
				<li><strong>Publico:</strong> 400, 700</li>
				<li><strong>Atlas:</strong> 300, 400, 500</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Headings</h3>
			<p>The following are the default sizes of the headings, h1, h3, etc.</p>
			<div class='example tk-atlas'>
				<h1>h1 heading example</h1>
				<h3>h3 heading example</h3>
				<h3>h3 heading example</h3>
				<h4>h4 heading example</h4>
				<h5>h5 heading example</h5>
				<h6>h6 heading example</h6>
			</div>
			<h3>Font size classes</h3>
			<p>Use the following convenience classes to size your text. They apply both <em>font-size</em> and <em>line-height</em>, so you may have to tweak depending on your needs.</p>
			<div class='example'>
				<p class='xxx-small'>.xxx-small (10px)</p>
				<p class='xx-small'>.xx-small (11px)</p>
				<p class='x-small'>.x-small (12px)</p>
				<p class='small'>.small (14px)</p>
				<p class='root'>.root (16px)</p>
				<p class='medium'>.medium (18px - default)</p>
				<p class='large'>.large (24px)</p>
				<p class='x-large'>.x-large (32px)</p>
				<p class='xx-large'>.xx-large (40px)</p>
				<p class='xxx-large'>.xxx-large (48px)</p>
				<p class='xxxx-large'>.xxxx-large (64px)</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id='prose'>
			<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Prose</h3>
			<p>Below is a typical setup for any prose sections. You can use the class "prose" for your div container, which will set the appropriate width and padding for optimal reading experience. You should use an h3 tag with class "prose__hed tk-atlas" if there is a title (aka hed).
			<div class='prose'>
				<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Title goes here</h3>
				<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. </p>
				<p>Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.</p>
			<div>
		</section>

		<section id='colors'>
			<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Colors</h3>
		</section>

		<section id='breakpoints'>
			<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Breakpoints</h3>
		</section>

		<section id='tables'>
			<h3 class='prose__hed tk-atlas'>Tables</h3>
		</section>

		<section id='buttons'>
